      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL SAKI (5) stalked the lead after a clean break from the tricky draw and went on to finish second (23.92) at this track in a Restricted WIN over 407m. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Rates highly and will give a great sight. POOKIE BEAR (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 5 lengths at this track in a handy 24.03 beating Boonie's Rose. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Should be in this for a long way. DIAMANTINA PEARL (6) was below best last time but prior to that was narrowly beaten when sixth (23.85) in a Grade 5 at this track. Can turn it around this time. LISSY'S GEM (2) can finish much closer after missing a cheque at this track last start.",
